  "prompt": "Can peppermint oil keep mice away?",
  "response": "Peppermint oil can be an effective natural deterrent for mice, as they dislike the strong smell. Here are some key points:\n\n1. How it works:\n- Mice have a sensitive sense of smell\n- Peppermint's strong scent is overwhelming and unpleasant to them\n- It can help repel mice from certain areas\n\n2. Application methods:\n- Soak cotton balls in peppermint oil\n- Place cotton balls in areas where mice are likely to enter\n- Refresh the oil every few weeks\n- Use peppermint essential oil spray around entry points\n\n3. Effectiveness:\n- Can be helpful as a temporary or preventive measure\n- Not a guaranteed permanent solution\n- Works best when combined with other mouse prevention strategies\n\n4. Additional prevention tips:\n- Seal entry points\n- Keep areas clean\n- Remove food sources\n- Use traps or professional pest control\n\nWhile peppermint oil can help, it's not 100% effective and should be used as part of a comprehensive mouse control strategy.",
